WEBVTT

00:00:08.813 --> 00:00:10.063
Court is now in session.

00:00:12.438 --> 00:00:14.063
Defendant, step forward.

00:00:16.146 --> 00:00:19.980
An attorney defends human rights
against authority.

00:00:21.271 --> 00:00:23.980
An attorney's mission
is to serve the people.

00:00:24.063 --> 00:00:25.313
Now, the defendant…

00:00:25.396 --> 00:00:28.146
But they can't serve everyone.

00:00:29.355 --> 00:00:32.771
An attorney can only protect their client,

00:00:33.646 --> 00:00:36.313
even if the client
is labeled a villain by society.

00:00:36.396 --> 00:00:37.980
The defendant

00:00:38.063 --> 00:00:39.396
is not guilty.

00:00:39.480 --> 00:00:40.813
Hooray!

00:00:40.896 --> 00:00:42.271
Order!

00:00:42.855 --> 00:00:46.021
When you save one,
you bring sorrow to another.

00:00:46.105 --> 00:00:47.646
You crooked lawyer!

00:00:48.146 --> 00:00:50.105
Defending someone like that…

00:00:50.188 --> 00:00:51.438
You're the devil too!

00:00:51.521 --> 00:00:53.980
Order in the court, please.

00:00:55.230 --> 00:00:59.230
An attorney always bears
the weight of this sin.

00:01:00.480 --> 00:01:01.771
And…

00:01:01.855 --> 00:01:03.271
Attorney Kujo.

00:01:04.063 --> 00:01:07.980
So you wear that attorney's badge
to protect evildoers, huh?

00:01:08.813 --> 00:01:10.021
Hey!

00:01:11.063 --> 00:01:11.980
Good attorneys

00:01:13.021 --> 00:01:14.521
have nasty personalities.

00:01:21.813 --> 00:01:24.938
TOKYO

00:01:29.063 --> 00:01:31.688
Oh, hello. Shinji Karasuma speaking.

00:01:34.896 --> 00:01:37.313
Are you sure this map is accurate?

00:01:42.146 --> 00:01:43.355
Hello?

00:01:44.771 --> 00:01:46.646
Are you listening, Ms. Yakushimae?

00:01:46.730 --> 00:01:49.355
Huh? Oh, yes. Whatcha got?

00:01:49.438 --> 00:01:52.688
I have no idea where I'm going
with this map you drew.

00:01:52.771 --> 00:01:55.938
What do you mean?
I drew it in detail, didn't I?

00:01:56.896 --> 00:01:58.605
How is this detailed--

00:02:00.021 --> 00:02:02.938
See? You just tripped, didn't you?

00:02:03.021 --> 00:02:05.021
-Didn't I draw that?
-What?

00:02:05.688 --> 00:02:07.396
NARROW, CATS, TOILET, GRILLED MEAT

00:02:07.480 --> 00:02:09.021
UNEVEN GROUND!

00:02:09.896 --> 00:02:12.521
Anyway, just give me the address.
I'll use a map app.

00:02:12.605 --> 00:02:16.021
I'm telling you, that's the quickest way.

00:02:16.105 --> 00:02:17.938
You're almost there.

00:02:20.730 --> 00:02:26.521
NO ILLEGAL PARKING

00:02:26.605 --> 00:02:28.730
I found it. New City 21 Building.

00:02:28.813 --> 00:02:31.105
Okay. Just go inside.

00:02:31.605 --> 00:02:32.813
What? Inside?

00:02:38.646 --> 00:02:40.063
Are you sure it's here?

00:02:40.730 --> 00:02:42.813
Sorry. I'm a bit busy, so I'm hanging up.

00:02:42.896 --> 00:02:43.730
Hold on a sec.

00:02:43.813 --> 00:02:44.896
Hello?

00:02:45.563 --> 00:02:46.688
Hello?

00:02:46.771 --> 00:02:47.771
Excuse me.

00:03:05.771 --> 00:03:07.021
KUJO LAW OFFICE
THIS WAY

00:03:07.105 --> 00:03:08.480
There it is.

00:03:36.355 --> 00:03:40.980
KUJO LAW OFFICE
IF YOU NEED ME, I'M ON THE ROOF

00:04:13.730 --> 00:04:16.105
Excuse me, but are you Attorney Kujo?

00:04:17.521 --> 00:04:20.980
-I'm Shinji Karasuma. I phoned earlier.
-Just a moment, please.

00:04:36.063 --> 00:04:37.105
What are you…

00:04:37.605 --> 00:04:38.438
Lunch.

00:04:39.980 --> 00:04:41.646
Hamburger steak with a fried egg.

00:04:43.563 --> 00:04:44.438
Want some?

00:04:45.021 --> 00:04:47.146
Oh, no, no… I'm good.

00:04:48.605 --> 00:04:50.438
Well, is this place…?

00:04:50.938 --> 00:04:52.230
My house.

00:04:52.938 --> 00:04:53.938
Your house?

00:04:54.688 --> 00:04:56.271
This is where I live.

00:05:04.813 --> 00:05:07.813
So have you had a chance
to go over my résumé?

00:05:07.896 --> 00:05:09.146
No, I haven't.

00:05:09.230 --> 00:05:10.396
What…?

00:05:10.896 --> 00:05:13.021
But I heard about you from Ms. Yakushimae.

00:05:13.605 --> 00:05:16.396
Top graduate of the Faculty of Law,
University of Tokyo.

00:05:16.480 --> 00:05:19.688
Employed at one of the Big Four firms,
Higashimura Yuhi Law Firm.

00:05:21.605 --> 00:05:24.313
With such great experience,
why do you wanna work here?

00:05:30.063 --> 00:05:31.188
Have you seen this?

00:05:33.563 --> 00:05:34.563
CROOKED LAWYER

00:05:34.646 --> 00:05:37.605
Do you know that people call you
a crooked lawyer?

00:05:39.813 --> 00:05:42.730
Like gang-led fraud schemes
or violent biker gang assaults…

00:05:42.813 --> 00:05:44.980
To put it bluntly,

00:05:45.480 --> 00:05:47.855
why do you always defend bad guys?

00:05:49.855 --> 00:05:51.230
Attorney Karasuma.

00:05:51.730 --> 00:05:52.605
Yes?

00:05:54.813 --> 00:05:56.855
Is this my interview?

00:05:58.063 --> 00:05:58.938
Oh, no…

00:05:59.438 --> 00:06:01.188
I didn't mean it like that.

00:06:39.521 --> 00:06:41.521
Mibu!

00:06:41.605 --> 00:06:43.271
Morita, we're closed today.

00:06:43.355 --> 00:06:44.730
I'm sorry.

00:06:44.813 --> 00:06:46.521
I had a bit of an accident.

00:06:46.605 --> 00:06:50.188
Can you fix it so I can take my girlfriend
out for a drive this weekend?

00:06:51.063 --> 00:06:52.105
No can do.

00:06:53.188 --> 00:06:56.188
Hit-and-run, right?
You're definitely gonna get caught.

00:06:56.271 --> 00:06:57.105
What?

00:06:57.188 --> 00:07:00.230
This dent's from a crash
you couldn't avoid.

00:07:00.730 --> 00:07:01.938
The paint's chipped too.

00:07:02.896 --> 00:07:05.771
With that, they can tell
the car's color, year, and model.

00:07:09.188 --> 00:07:11.396
Your car may not be
on the crash-site camera,

00:07:11.480 --> 00:07:14.438
but it'll definitely show up
on other cameras nearby.

00:07:16.688 --> 00:07:18.396
The police will catch you soon.

00:07:21.605 --> 00:07:24.063
Seriously?

00:07:25.605 --> 00:07:27.646
What should I do, Mibu?

00:07:32.646 --> 00:07:34.480
I'll introduce you to a lawyer.

00:07:38.896 --> 00:07:40.105
Thank you for the meal.

00:07:43.396 --> 00:07:44.605
Attorney Kujo.

00:07:45.438 --> 00:07:47.313
KENGO MIBU

00:07:48.521 --> 00:07:50.063
Yes, Kujo speaking.

00:07:50.146 --> 00:07:51.813
Attorney Kujo.

00:07:52.396 --> 00:07:55.188
I've got a favor to ask.
It's kind of urgent.

00:07:57.855 --> 00:07:59.771
I see. Understood. I'll be waiting.

00:08:02.855 --> 00:08:03.980
A defense request?

00:08:04.063 --> 00:08:04.980
Yes.

00:08:06.021 --> 00:08:07.855
It's a traffic accident, apparently.

00:08:07.938 --> 00:08:09.105
I'll help.

00:08:10.188 --> 00:08:11.688
Thank you very much.

00:08:15.021 --> 00:08:17.896
Then, can you take this?

00:08:17.980 --> 00:08:18.980
Huh?

00:08:19.063 --> 00:08:20.730
You just said that you'd help.

00:08:22.563 --> 00:08:24.021
The sink's that way.

00:08:46.688 --> 00:08:48.480
I've finished, Attorney Kujo.

00:08:48.563 --> 00:08:49.813
Thank you very much.

00:08:50.813 --> 00:08:52.521
So is this place…

00:08:53.313 --> 00:08:57.146
It used to be a night pub,
and I rented it as is.

00:08:57.646 --> 00:08:59.230
Use the space around there.

00:09:00.271 --> 00:09:02.646
Around here?

00:09:08.605 --> 00:09:11.271
Oh, Ms. Yakushimae uses that
when she comes, so…

00:09:30.688 --> 00:09:32.688
-Sorry for the short notice.
-Oh.

00:09:33.188 --> 00:09:34.896
-Please.
-Oh.

00:09:36.646 --> 00:09:37.480
Who's this?

00:09:39.355 --> 00:09:41.730
My name is Shinji Karasuma,
and I'm an attorney.

00:09:41.813 --> 00:09:43.105
An attorney?

00:09:44.688 --> 00:09:46.188
Please rest assured

00:09:46.813 --> 00:09:49.146
that he's way more competent than I am.

00:09:50.855 --> 00:09:52.855
-Attorney Karasuma.
-Yes?

00:09:53.730 --> 00:09:54.730
Serve them some tea.

00:09:55.271 --> 00:09:56.105
What?

00:10:00.938 --> 00:10:01.813
Please.

00:10:01.896 --> 00:10:02.730
Sure.

00:10:06.980 --> 00:10:08.438
Oh, okay.

00:10:15.855 --> 00:10:17.188
So,

00:10:17.271 --> 00:10:18.855
what's the situation?

00:10:23.771 --> 00:10:24.938
Morita,

00:10:26.480 --> 00:10:27.438
explain it to him.

00:10:29.230 --> 00:10:30.355
Yes.

00:10:31.896 --> 00:10:32.771
Um,

00:10:33.730 --> 00:10:38.771
I was driving my car,
and I accidentally hit something.

00:10:39.646 --> 00:10:40.646
What exactly was it?

00:10:41.730 --> 00:10:42.855
Um,

00:10:43.521 --> 00:10:44.730
well…

00:11:02.063 --> 00:11:04.271
Please tell me honestly.

00:11:07.730 --> 00:11:10.063
It's an attorney's duty

00:11:10.855 --> 00:11:12.730
to protect their client.

00:11:43.063 --> 00:11:45.063
Were you on your smartphone at the time?

00:11:45.646 --> 00:11:46.938
No, well…

00:11:47.021 --> 00:11:49.271
You smell like alcohol.

00:11:49.355 --> 00:11:50.688
Were you driving drunk?

00:11:50.771 --> 00:11:53.605
What? No, of course not.

00:11:54.771 --> 00:11:55.813
It's okay.

00:11:56.313 --> 00:11:58.438
We're the only ones listening.

00:12:09.813 --> 00:12:11.396
I'm sorry.

00:12:11.480 --> 00:12:14.980
I happened to see
a rare character on my phone.

00:12:15.980 --> 00:12:18.563
And I was drinking until noon.

00:12:18.646 --> 00:12:21.313
Drunk driving and gaming?

00:12:21.396 --> 00:12:22.688
Quite the scumbag.

00:12:23.396 --> 00:12:24.480
Attorney Karasuma.

00:12:24.563 --> 00:12:26.980
If the police reach out
to the game company,

00:12:27.063 --> 00:12:29.813
they can trace when and where
you were playing the game.

00:12:29.896 --> 00:12:32.146
You shouldn't say you were playing a game.

00:12:32.230 --> 00:12:33.646
Oh… Okay.

00:12:33.730 --> 00:12:38.313
Um, if the person I hit died,
would the charges be more serious?

00:12:40.771 --> 00:12:41.980
Excuse me.

00:12:42.063 --> 00:12:43.688
I have severe allergic rhinitis.

00:12:44.980 --> 00:12:48.230
If you were driving under the influence,
speeding, and distracted,

00:12:48.313 --> 00:12:49.646
it'd be dangerous driving,

00:12:49.730 --> 00:12:51.730
punishable by up to 20 years in prison.

00:12:51.813 --> 00:12:55.146
If it's negligent driving causing death,
you'd get a suspended sentence.

00:12:55.230 --> 00:12:57.355
Whether it's dangerous
or negligent driving

00:12:57.438 --> 00:12:59.105
will determine your future.

00:13:00.230 --> 00:13:01.771
It'll depend on Attorney Kujo.

00:13:04.896 --> 00:13:06.438
What…

00:13:07.563 --> 00:13:09.563
No way, Mibu!

00:13:09.646 --> 00:13:12.771
I don't wanna end up
in prison for 20 years.

00:13:13.355 --> 00:13:14.855
Damn it.

00:13:15.355 --> 00:13:18.188
I really hope
the guy I hit is still alive.

00:13:20.188 --> 00:13:22.521
The victim's statement
can complicate the case.

00:13:23.605 --> 00:13:24.438
Huh?

00:13:25.896 --> 00:13:28.021
So it's better if the victim is dead.

00:13:29.896 --> 00:13:32.063
Attorney Kujo's seriously messed up.

00:13:32.771 --> 00:13:34.563
Then they can't take a statement.

00:13:35.146 --> 00:13:38.021
With no objective evidence
to prove anything, we can win.

00:13:38.105 --> 00:13:39.480
Give me your phone.

00:13:42.313 --> 00:13:44.730
I'm gonna talk to myself out loud.

00:13:44.813 --> 00:13:46.188
Talk to yourself?

00:13:46.271 --> 00:13:48.146
A smartphone holds a lot of evidence.

00:13:48.230 --> 00:13:50.063
Let's leave it here.

00:13:50.146 --> 00:13:53.813
If the police ask you to hand over
your smartphone, tell them you lost it.

00:13:53.896 --> 00:13:54.938
Your wallet.

00:13:57.105 --> 00:13:59.438
If you have bar receipts,
throw them all away.

00:13:59.521 --> 00:14:01.563
Oh, okay.

00:14:02.313 --> 00:14:04.730
Turn yourself in
once you're completely sober.

00:14:05.313 --> 00:14:07.646
A detox drug, Tathion,
helps eliminate alcohol.

00:14:07.730 --> 00:14:09.355
It's effective, even for meth,

00:14:09.438 --> 00:14:11.938
but is typically
only prescribed in hospitals.

00:14:12.021 --> 00:14:13.063
So,

00:14:13.730 --> 00:14:15.646
go to a sauna and sweat it out.

00:14:15.730 --> 00:14:17.813
A sauna? Got it.

00:14:18.563 --> 00:14:21.063
It's late, but going to the police
with an attorney

00:14:21.146 --> 00:14:22.980
still counts as turning yourself in.

00:14:24.146 --> 00:14:25.646
Listen, Mr. Morita.

00:14:26.313 --> 00:14:30.230
Regarding the location of the collision,
the traffic light color, or the speed,

00:14:30.313 --> 00:14:32.730
you can't make any statements about them.

00:14:32.813 --> 00:14:37.105
Still, if you show up and stay silent,
it's going to look suspicious.

00:14:37.813 --> 00:14:40.521
So you'll admit to hitting something.

00:14:40.605 --> 00:14:44.021
But refrain from saying anything further.
That's the safest approach.

00:14:44.105 --> 00:14:45.105
Okay.

00:14:45.771 --> 00:14:48.313
During the questioning
at the police station,

00:14:48.396 --> 00:14:51.438
there's only one thing you should do.

00:14:51.521 --> 00:14:52.355
Huh?

00:14:54.563 --> 00:14:56.813
Don't say anything unnecessary.

00:14:57.980 --> 00:14:59.396
That's all.

00:15:00.646 --> 00:15:02.563
Understood, sir.

00:15:03.480 --> 00:15:04.605
It's going to be okay.

00:15:05.896 --> 00:15:07.313
You'll be out after 20 days.

00:15:09.105 --> 00:15:10.105
I'll be out?

00:15:10.813 --> 00:15:12.771
You'll be released.

00:15:17.271 --> 00:15:19.730
Ryota? Ryota, can you hear me?

00:15:20.438 --> 00:15:23.563
-He's becoming less responsive.
-Okay. Attaching the ECG leads.

00:15:23.646 --> 00:15:25.396
Putting on the blood pressure cuff.

00:15:25.480 --> 00:15:27.355
Excuse me for a second.

00:15:36.813 --> 00:15:38.105
Mrs. Minegishi,

00:15:38.605 --> 00:15:39.938
how's your son?

00:15:41.563 --> 00:15:43.188
He's still in surgery.

00:15:44.438 --> 00:15:45.646
I see.

00:15:48.563 --> 00:15:49.480
But

00:15:50.896 --> 00:15:51.896
my husband…

00:15:53.438 --> 00:15:54.855
My husband…

00:15:54.938 --> 00:15:57.188
They said he died instantly.

00:16:11.271 --> 00:16:12.271
JAPAN'S TOP TAKOYAKI

00:16:12.355 --> 00:16:13.896
"Japan's top takoyaki!"

00:16:15.063 --> 00:16:15.980
Yes?

00:16:17.188 --> 00:16:20.146
The sign we just saw said,
"Japan's top takoyaki," right?

00:16:21.271 --> 00:16:23.105
Oh, did it?

00:16:24.355 --> 00:16:27.396
Well, doesn't it make you want to try it?

00:16:27.480 --> 00:16:29.271
No, not particularly.

00:16:29.771 --> 00:16:33.313
It's unclear what defines it
as the best in Japan anyway.

00:16:33.396 --> 00:16:35.480
Self-proclaiming it isn't enough?

00:16:35.563 --> 00:16:38.438
But are they using
"Japan's top" or "world's first"

00:16:38.521 --> 00:16:40.480
in ads without objective evidence?

00:16:40.563 --> 00:16:44.730
It may defy the Unjustifiable Premiums Act
or the Unfair Competition Prevention Act.

00:16:44.813 --> 00:16:46.105
So straitlaced.

00:16:47.021 --> 00:16:50.438
-Great educational background.
-It's nothing to do with my education.

00:16:50.521 --> 00:16:52.771
I feel uneasy
when things aren't well defined.

00:16:52.855 --> 00:16:56.230
Then what about "Japan's Funniest Osaki"?

00:16:56.313 --> 00:16:57.521
What's that?

00:16:58.021 --> 00:16:59.271
You don't know?

00:16:59.855 --> 00:17:02.730
There's a comedian duo called "Champions,"

00:17:02.813 --> 00:17:06.146
and the straight man calls himself
"Japan's Funniest Osaki."

00:17:06.230 --> 00:17:07.646
Is that a crime too?

00:17:07.730 --> 00:17:09.480
Yes, if he's not Japan's funniest.

00:17:09.563 --> 00:17:12.938
-What about "Nabeatsu of the World"?
-Nabeatsu?

00:17:13.021 --> 00:17:17.313
He now goes by Sando Katsura.
He was the funny man of the duo Jarism.

00:17:17.396 --> 00:17:22.480
He was all the rage for a counting gag,
acting goofy at every multiple of three

00:17:22.563 --> 00:17:23.938
or any number with a three.

00:17:24.021 --> 00:17:28.146
He calls himself "Nabeatsu of the World,"
but it's not a claim to being number one.

00:17:28.230 --> 00:17:29.563
It doesn't break the law--

00:17:29.646 --> 00:17:30.896
Hey!

00:17:32.105 --> 00:17:35.396
What the hell have you guys
been rambling on about?

00:17:36.021 --> 00:17:40.271
I couldn't care less
about takoyaki or comedians!

00:17:40.355 --> 00:17:42.938
I'm about to turn myself in to the police!

00:17:43.730 --> 00:17:46.521
Can't you shut up for a bit?

00:17:48.021 --> 00:17:48.855
I mean,

00:17:49.480 --> 00:17:51.605
I couldn't say this in front of Mibu,

00:17:51.688 --> 00:17:54.688
but are you sure you can handle this?

00:17:56.646 --> 00:17:58.021
So should we call it off?

00:18:00.313 --> 00:18:01.146
Huh?

00:18:01.230 --> 00:18:04.063
But then you'll spend the next 20 years

00:18:04.146 --> 00:18:08.730
unable to eat takoyaki
or watch comedy shows whenever you want.

00:18:10.813 --> 00:18:12.146
Are you going with me

00:18:13.438 --> 00:18:14.480
or not going?

00:18:16.938 --> 00:18:19.605
Take control of your own life.

00:18:24.855 --> 00:18:28.063
CHINESE CUISINE
BEIJING RESTAURANT

00:18:28.146 --> 00:18:30.271
Wow. So you're the representative now.

00:18:30.355 --> 00:18:31.188
Yeah.

00:18:32.230 --> 00:18:35.188
The previous representative
retired due to old age,

00:18:35.688 --> 00:18:36.730
so I took over.

00:18:36.813 --> 00:18:38.688
That's impressive.

00:18:39.188 --> 00:18:43.146
Your organization helps victims and
offenders reintegrate into society, right?

00:18:43.230 --> 00:18:44.063
Yeah.

00:18:44.146 --> 00:18:47.105
That's a job you can't do without passion.

00:18:47.771 --> 00:18:50.688
We support the offenders
so they don't commit crimes again.

00:18:50.771 --> 00:18:51.855
It's not passion.

00:18:51.938 --> 00:18:52.813
Then what is it?

00:18:53.563 --> 00:18:57.980
I want people to be able to go
to a convenience store late at night.

00:18:58.063 --> 00:19:00.730
And I don't want to become
a victim of crime myself.

00:19:01.771 --> 00:19:04.646
It's my own way
of preventing crime, I guess.

00:19:07.688 --> 00:19:08.521
Excuse me.

00:19:08.605 --> 00:19:12.480
One plate of gyoza,
pork and pepper stir-fry,

00:19:12.563 --> 00:19:14.438
and lettuce and egg fried rice.

00:19:14.521 --> 00:19:15.813
Oh, I'm already…

00:19:15.896 --> 00:19:17.438
I'm going to eat it.

00:19:17.521 --> 00:19:19.938
I've got to eat when I can,
or I won't hold up.

00:19:20.021 --> 00:19:20.855
I see.

00:19:20.938 --> 00:19:22.271
-Make it a large.
-Okay.

00:19:22.355 --> 00:19:23.980
Thank you.

00:19:26.021 --> 00:19:26.896
That aside,

00:19:27.605 --> 00:19:29.980
you've got something
to talk to me about, right?

00:19:30.063 --> 00:19:30.896
Whatcha got?

00:19:30.980 --> 00:19:33.980
I wanted to thank you
for connecting me with Attorney Kujo.

00:19:34.813 --> 00:19:35.980
How did it go?

00:19:37.188 --> 00:19:40.105
I guess I'm currently
in the probationary period.

00:19:40.188 --> 00:19:41.646
But are you actually serious?

00:19:41.730 --> 00:19:46.146
I mean, being an attorney under someone
who could lose their badge any day…

00:19:46.646 --> 00:19:47.980
I want to find out

00:19:48.063 --> 00:19:52.271
whether Attorney Kujo
is a good attorney or a bad one.

00:19:55.771 --> 00:19:57.313
You wanna ask me why, right?

00:19:57.396 --> 00:20:00.146
My answer sounded like
there's some kind of backstory.

00:20:02.146 --> 00:20:03.730
Good attorneys…

00:20:04.230 --> 00:20:05.771
have nasty personalities.

00:20:06.521 --> 00:20:08.730
-What?
-It's my personal theory.

00:20:09.313 --> 00:20:11.980
-And Attorney Kujo?
-You're trying to figure that out.

00:20:12.063 --> 00:20:13.355
I don't know why, though.

00:20:13.980 --> 00:20:15.063
Yeah.

00:20:15.146 --> 00:20:17.730
Well, let me know if you find out.

00:20:18.730 --> 00:20:19.771
Yes, ma'am.

00:20:22.021 --> 00:20:26.063
Did you know that he kept
his ex-wife's last name after the divorce?

00:20:26.146 --> 00:20:27.813
What? No.

00:20:27.896 --> 00:20:29.688
I think they have a daughter.

00:20:29.771 --> 00:20:33.355
And when they got divorced,
he gave her all his assets.

00:20:33.438 --> 00:20:35.813
Wow, he's a good person.

00:20:36.313 --> 00:20:38.646
That means Attorney Kujo is…

00:20:38.730 --> 00:20:40.480
Here's your gyoza.

00:20:40.563 --> 00:20:41.980
That was fast!

00:20:42.063 --> 00:20:43.980
-Thank you.
-There you go.

00:20:44.063 --> 00:20:45.188
-Oh, can you…
-Sorry.

00:20:45.271 --> 00:20:46.146
Here.

00:20:46.771 --> 00:20:48.521
Boss, it's so delicious.

00:20:48.605 --> 00:20:49.438
Thank you.

00:20:51.396 --> 00:20:53.980
Mmm, it looks delicious.

00:21:06.313 --> 00:21:07.646
Good morning.

00:21:08.146 --> 00:21:09.230
Good morning.

00:21:10.146 --> 00:21:12.063
Is that your breakfast, Attorney Kujo?

00:21:12.146 --> 00:21:12.980
Yes.

00:21:18.646 --> 00:21:20.105
Well, then.

00:21:20.188 --> 00:21:22.480
-Do your best with Morita's case.
-Okay.

00:21:26.813 --> 00:21:29.730
I hope you give it your best too,
Attorney Karasuma.

00:21:29.813 --> 00:21:30.813
Huh?

00:21:31.980 --> 00:21:32.813
Oh…

00:21:33.313 --> 00:21:34.146
Yes.

00:21:43.730 --> 00:21:46.271
What does Mibu do for a living?

00:21:46.855 --> 00:21:49.855
Officially, he runs an auto repair shop,

00:21:49.938 --> 00:21:52.980
but he seems to have ties
to anti-social groups.

00:21:53.063 --> 00:21:55.855
Do we need to get along
with people like him?

00:21:57.230 --> 00:21:59.480
Do I look like I'm close with him?

00:22:00.688 --> 00:22:01.771
Yes.

00:22:03.021 --> 00:22:04.980
Oh, speaking of which…

00:22:06.938 --> 00:22:10.188
How did Morita's police questioning
about the traffic accident go?

00:22:12.771 --> 00:22:14.813
It all went smoothly as planned.

00:22:15.855 --> 00:22:17.563
All right. Let's go.

00:22:19.646 --> 00:22:23.188
The victims were the father,
Masato Minegishi, aged 35,

00:22:23.271 --> 00:22:25.188
and his son, Ryota, aged 6.

00:22:25.271 --> 00:22:27.896
The accident happened
on their way home from nursery.

00:22:29.021 --> 00:22:31.230
The father had been suffering
from depression

00:22:31.313 --> 00:22:32.688
and was on leave from work.

00:22:32.771 --> 00:22:34.605
Depression, huh?

00:22:35.396 --> 00:22:37.146
And how is the father doing?

00:22:37.230 --> 00:22:38.688
He died.

00:22:40.355 --> 00:22:42.271
But something caught my attention.

00:22:42.938 --> 00:22:46.896
The victim's bicycle,
captured on Morita's dashcam,

00:22:46.980 --> 00:22:48.605
was already lying on the ground.

00:22:48.688 --> 00:22:50.063
It was already lying there?

00:22:50.563 --> 00:22:53.230
Also, the scene investigators
and the medical examiner

00:22:53.980 --> 00:22:56.230
said the child was bleeding.

00:22:56.313 --> 00:23:00.271
But there were no signs of bleeding
or vital reactions in the father's body.

00:23:00.355 --> 00:23:01.438
What…

00:23:01.521 --> 00:23:06.146
If he'd been alive when he was hit,
he should've bled significantly, right?

00:23:06.230 --> 00:23:07.480
You're right.

00:23:07.563 --> 00:23:08.730
So,

00:23:09.855 --> 00:23:11.230
something felt off.

00:23:11.313 --> 00:23:14.980
I looked into the medical records
from the hospital he'd been visiting.

00:23:17.730 --> 00:23:21.396
He'd previously been rushed
to the hospital for a cardiac condition

00:23:21.480 --> 00:23:25.271
and was prescribed heart medication.

00:23:25.355 --> 00:23:27.813
A cardiac condition?

00:23:30.563 --> 00:23:34.438
There's a possibility
that he had a heart attack,

00:23:34.938 --> 00:23:37.896
collapsed on the road,
and died before Morita hit him.

00:23:39.896 --> 00:23:40.730
Hold on.

00:23:41.355 --> 00:23:45.521
So are you saying that the father's death
had nothing to do with the accident?

00:23:45.605 --> 00:23:47.146
If that's the case,

00:23:47.855 --> 00:23:51.480
the destruction of the corpse
due to Morita's negligence isn't a crime.

00:23:51.563 --> 00:23:55.438
If he was already dead, it wouldn't be
negligent driving causing death either.

00:23:55.521 --> 00:23:57.355
But Morita drank in broad daylight

00:23:57.438 --> 00:24:00.063
and was distracted while driving
because of a game.

00:24:00.146 --> 00:24:03.396
Just as you said, he is quite the scumbag.

00:24:03.480 --> 00:24:05.855
So you do think so, too,
Attorney Kujo. Then--

00:24:05.938 --> 00:24:09.146
But whether or not he's a scumbag
is irrelevant right now.

00:24:09.646 --> 00:24:12.480
Whether the father was alive or dead
when Morita hit him…

00:24:12.563 --> 00:24:14.271
That's all that matters.

00:24:17.771 --> 00:24:18.605
And…

00:24:19.605 --> 00:24:21.313
how is his 6-year-old son doing?

00:24:24.813 --> 00:24:26.896
There were no life-threatening injuries.

00:24:28.730 --> 00:24:29.563
It's just…

00:24:32.938 --> 00:24:35.146
His left leg was amputated.

00:24:42.980 --> 00:24:44.605
Ryota.

00:24:50.188 --> 00:24:51.771
I'm sorry.

00:24:54.521 --> 00:24:56.521
I'm sorry.

00:25:29.271 --> 00:25:30.105
The verdict…

00:25:30.188 --> 00:25:31.021
COURTHOUSE

00:25:31.105 --> 00:25:35.313
The defendant is sentenced
to one year and eight months in prison.

00:25:35.396 --> 00:25:38.730
Execution of the sentence
is suspended for three years

00:25:38.813 --> 00:25:41.521
from the date this judgment
becomes final and binding.

00:25:42.855 --> 00:25:43.730
Huh?

00:25:44.271 --> 00:25:47.105
For real? The sentence is suspended?

00:25:47.188 --> 00:25:48.688
Wait, no slammer for me?

00:25:48.771 --> 00:25:50.938
Defendant, mind your language.

00:25:52.188 --> 00:25:55.271
The following are the reasons
for the verdict.

00:25:56.396 --> 00:25:59.980
On April 1st, 2025,

00:26:00.063 --> 00:26:04.980
the defendant was driving
a standard passenger vehicle

00:26:05.063 --> 00:26:09.521
near 6-14-5, Koto Ward, Tokyo.

00:26:09.605 --> 00:26:14.521
He was heading northeast
from a southwest direction.

00:26:18.730 --> 00:26:22.021
Thanks a bunch, sir!

00:26:22.563 --> 00:26:23.771
Morita.

00:26:24.688 --> 00:26:28.438
You're being treated to grilled meat
and a hostess club for your release!

00:26:28.521 --> 00:26:29.855
For real? Meat?

00:26:29.938 --> 00:26:32.855
-Yeah.
-It's been ages.

00:26:32.938 --> 00:26:34.938
I'm dying for a freezing cold beer!

00:26:40.813 --> 00:26:44.396
The accident occurred postmortem,
so Morita's not been held accountable.

00:26:44.896 --> 00:26:45.938
But

00:26:46.896 --> 00:26:48.938
apparently, they didn't hire a lawyer,

00:26:49.021 --> 00:26:52.480
so the insurance company told them
to settle under the standard terms.

00:26:53.480 --> 00:26:55.438
One leg of a child…

00:26:55.938 --> 00:26:59.146
It's a Grade 4, Category 5 disability,
yet they settled for 40 million.

00:27:00.688 --> 00:27:03.480
Ignorance is truly a sin, isn't it?

00:27:03.563 --> 00:27:06.146
Attorney Kujo, how can you say that here?

00:27:06.230 --> 00:27:07.938
Both Ryota and his mother…

00:27:08.438 --> 00:27:11.105
lost their father and husband
in such a way.

00:27:12.063 --> 00:27:16.396
If we defended the victim, we'd claim
lost future earnings and compensation.

00:27:16.480 --> 00:27:18.355
We could've secured over 100 million,

00:27:18.438 --> 00:27:22.771
and about five million more for six months
of hospitalization and outpatient care.

00:27:22.855 --> 00:27:26.730
Yet, because of someone like that man,
their lives have been changed forever.

00:27:26.813 --> 00:27:28.480
Attorney Karasuma,

00:27:28.563 --> 00:27:32.063
an attorney should not act
based on personal beliefs or convictions.

00:27:32.563 --> 00:27:35.146
I separate law and morality
in my thinking.

00:27:35.230 --> 00:27:37.646
Even if something is morally unacceptable,

00:27:37.730 --> 00:27:40.230
an attorney's mission
is to protect their client.

00:27:41.771 --> 00:27:42.938
However,

00:27:44.021 --> 00:27:47.688
when you protect your client,
you bring sorrow to the other party.

00:27:50.188 --> 00:27:55.230
We attorneys must carry the weight
of that sin throughout our lives.

00:28:04.146 --> 00:28:06.271
Did you defend an anti-social individual?

00:28:06.355 --> 00:28:08.521
How much did you get paid for this case?

00:28:08.605 --> 00:28:13.688
Attorney Kujo, if I'm ever in trouble,
make sure you defend me.

00:28:55.855 --> 00:28:58.730
TRAFFIC ACCIDENT CLAIMS
STANDARDS FOR CALCULATING DAMAGES

00:29:00.896 --> 00:29:03.063
LIST OF VERDICTS FOR NEGLIGENT DRIVING

00:29:30.605 --> 00:29:32.188
Ms. Yakushimae?

00:29:33.146 --> 00:29:35.396
Bit by bit… Yes.

00:29:35.480 --> 00:29:36.813
As I said over the phone…

00:29:36.896 --> 00:29:38.438
There we go.

00:29:38.521 --> 00:29:40.688
But I don't think it's possible.

00:29:41.896 --> 00:29:45.938
I understand that once a settlement has
been reached with the insurance company,

00:29:46.021 --> 00:29:48.355
it's quite difficult to overturn it.

00:29:48.855 --> 00:29:53.855
But how about filing a lawsuit
regarding your son's insurance?

00:29:57.771 --> 00:29:59.813
I know a very reliable attorney.

00:30:00.688 --> 00:30:02.063
It doesn't matter anymore.

00:30:04.938 --> 00:30:06.688
I've lost the will to keep going.

00:30:06.771 --> 00:30:08.980
That might be the case for you…

00:30:11.355 --> 00:30:13.855
but Ryota probably doesn't feel
the same way.

00:30:18.271 --> 00:30:22.813
He has to live on for decades to come.

00:30:24.813 --> 00:30:26.605
For the sake of your son,

00:30:27.355 --> 00:30:29.146
let's retry the case.

00:30:59.855 --> 00:31:01.771
I told her.

00:31:01.855 --> 00:31:02.938
What?

00:31:03.021 --> 00:31:06.230
I passed on the message word-for-word,
without any mistakes.

00:31:06.313 --> 00:31:08.105
Please tell Attorney Kujo that.

00:31:15.396 --> 00:31:17.521
Let's do just a little bit more, okay?

00:31:18.271 --> 00:31:19.688
-Please.
-Okay.

00:31:34.146 --> 00:31:36.480
I spoke to Ms. Yakushimae at the hospital.

00:31:37.480 --> 00:31:39.521
You asked her to do that, didn't you?

00:31:40.021 --> 00:31:43.938
You asked her to tell Mr. Minegishi's wife
to retry the case for her son.

00:31:45.230 --> 00:31:49.521
And you even wrote a referral letter
to your mentor, Attorney Nagaragi.

00:31:50.563 --> 00:31:55.271
If you wanted to help them, you should've
just refused to defend the bad guy.

00:31:56.605 --> 00:31:59.521
Just what kind of emotions
are driving your actions?

00:32:00.438 --> 00:32:01.605
Attorney Karasuma,

00:32:02.980 --> 00:32:04.688
I'll say it as often as it takes.

00:32:05.313 --> 00:32:08.146
An attorney defends human rights
against authority.

00:32:08.230 --> 00:32:10.646
An attorney's mission
is to protect their client.

00:32:10.730 --> 00:32:13.480
I'm not asking
for a general answer like that.

00:32:14.021 --> 00:32:16.313
I'm asking about your emotions.

00:32:24.063 --> 00:32:26.563
Why did you decide to practice law,
Attorney Kujo?

00:32:29.730 --> 00:32:32.146
Are you interviewing me again?

00:32:37.355 --> 00:32:39.938
Then let me ask you in return.

00:32:40.813 --> 00:32:43.480
Why did you decide to practice law,
Attorney Karasuma?

00:32:44.563 --> 00:32:47.105
As a top graduate
of the University of Tokyo,

00:32:47.188 --> 00:32:48.855
you could've been a bureaucrat.

00:32:51.855 --> 00:32:55.521
It goes back to when I attended
the trial for a certain case.

00:32:56.855 --> 00:32:58.188
Eighteen years ago,

00:32:58.271 --> 00:33:02.146
I attended a trial where the defendant
killed solely to get the death penalty.

00:33:02.230 --> 00:33:04.480
I was in elementary school.

00:33:04.563 --> 00:33:07.813
I couldn't understand
the motives of the killer

00:33:07.896 --> 00:33:10.855
or the emotions of the victims.

00:33:10.938 --> 00:33:13.730
Meanwhile, only the law
remained clear and functioning.

00:33:16.105 --> 00:33:17.271
I see.

00:33:18.938 --> 00:33:23.271
I decided to seek the meaning of life
through learning about the law

00:33:23.355 --> 00:33:25.480
and everything connected to it.

00:33:29.355 --> 00:33:30.688
Is that so?

00:33:32.396 --> 00:33:33.480
That trial…

00:33:41.188 --> 00:33:43.355
I attended it too.

00:33:44.230 --> 00:33:45.771
I know.

00:33:46.438 --> 00:33:47.688
That's why I came here.

00:33:49.938 --> 00:33:51.938
I'm here because I find you interesting.

00:33:55.730 --> 00:33:57.980
I'll stick with you a little longer.

00:34:04.855 --> 00:34:05.813
Fine by me.

00:34:39.771 --> 00:34:40.855
Hey, Sogabe.

00:34:46.146 --> 00:34:47.313
Veggies.

00:34:49.813 --> 00:34:50.896
Deliver them.

00:34:50.980 --> 00:34:51.896
Okay.

00:34:52.396 --> 00:34:53.771
Later.

00:35:06.646 --> 00:35:08.230
Excuse me.

00:35:09.563 --> 00:35:11.188
Do you have a moment?

00:35:11.271 --> 00:35:12.105
Huh?

00:35:12.605 --> 00:35:14.396
What's in the bag?

00:35:15.980 --> 00:35:18.063
Uh, well, they're snacks.

00:35:18.146 --> 00:35:20.063
Do you mind if we check?

00:35:20.146 --> 00:35:21.605
Well, these are just snacks.

00:35:21.688 --> 00:35:24.521
-We'll confirm that.
-Oh, I'm sorry. Don't get mad at me.

00:35:24.605 --> 00:35:26.271
I'm not mad.

00:35:26.355 --> 00:35:28.813
May I have a moment?

00:35:29.771 --> 00:35:31.980
Hey, what are you filming?

00:35:32.063 --> 00:35:33.813
You're interfering with our duties.

00:35:35.063 --> 00:35:40.521
Filming for a legitimate reason
isn't considered interference with duties.

00:35:40.605 --> 00:35:44.188
This is for preserving evidence
in case of an unlawful investigation.

00:35:44.271 --> 00:35:46.021
Who the hell are you?

00:35:48.563 --> 00:35:50.396
I'm an attorney

00:35:50.980 --> 00:35:52.480
with a nasty personality.

00:38:34.021 --> 00:38:38.896
Subtitle translation by: Miho Kunisawa